718526f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 100th Street
718526f-a.text:
Central Park West, west side, north from 100th Street. This photograph shows very clearly the havoc with the construction of the Eighth Avenue subway played with Central Park West.
December 1925
Brown Brothers.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
718526f-a.folder: Central Park West & 100th Street, Manhattan, NY

718528f-b.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 100th Street
718528f-b.text:
(1)
Central Park West, west side, at 101st Street, seen from Central Park near the 100th Street entrance. The tall new apartment house (l926) is on the N.W. corner of 101st Street. The buildings on the S.W. corner have been demolished.
October 23, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NMg ~ 821
(2)
The same, a close view, showing principally the excavation at the S.W. corner and the houses on the north side of 101st Street. The small one, 10 West 101st Street, is the Community Hospital.
October 23, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.

718529f-a.text:

August 9, 1929.
